Curve Steepening Strategy¶

2y-10y has recently turned inverted. This notebook tries to reproduce works in "Catch A Wave" by Harley S. Bassman.

Other resources:

  • FT: What is the US yield curve and why has it spooked investors?
  • ZeroHedge: The 2s10s Just Inverted: Here's What Happens Next
  • SEC: Summary Prospectus - Quadratic Interest Rate Volatility and Inflation Hedge ETF
    IVOL should be the first ETF after GFC that offers retail access to swap spread options. The prospectus explained risks associated with swap spread options. IVOL uses options with shorter expiry (as of 08/30, IVOL holds option that will expire within one year).

import numpy

import pandas as pd
import pandas_datareader as pd_reader
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import datetime
import time
from pandas.plotting import register_matplotlib_converters
import requests_cache

############################## PRELUDE ##############################

# initiate converters
register_matplotlib_converters()

# rc config
plt.rcParams['figure.figsize'] = [20, 8]
plt.rcParams['figure.titlesize'] = 'large'
plt.rcParams['figure.titleweight'] = 'bold'
plt.rcParams['xtick.labelsize'] = plt.rcParams['ytick.labelsize'] = 15
plt.rcParams['axes.titlesize'] = 'large'
plt.rcParams['font.size'] = 20
plt.rcParams['font.weight'] = 'bold'
plt.rcParams['axes.labelweight'] = "bold"
plt.rcParams['axes.titlepad'] = 10
plt.rcParams['axes.titleweight'] = "bold"
plt.rcParams['legend.fontsize'] = 14
plt.rcParams["lines.linewidth"] = 2.5
plt.style.use('dark_background')

expire_after = datetime.timedelta(days=1)
session = requests_cache.CachedSession(cache_name='cache', backend='sqlite', expire_after=expire_after)

start = datetime.datetime(1990, 6, 1)
end = datetime.date.today()

def fred_reader(symbol, start = start):
    return pd_reader.data.DataReader(symbol, 'fred', start, end, session=session)

def draw_span(ax, begin, end, leftmost):
    if begin > leftmost:
        ax.axvspan(begin, end, color='tab:grey', alpha=0.3)

def plot_recession(ax, leftmost):
    try:
        recs = fred_reader('USREC', start = datetime.datetime(1920, 1, 1)).query('USREC==1')
        recs_90 = recs.loc['1990':'1991']
        recs90_bgn = recs_90.index[0]
        recs90_end = recs_90.index[-1]
        draw_span(ax, recs90_bgn, recs90_end, leftmost)
        recs_2k = recs.loc['2001']
        recs2k_bgn = recs_2k.index[0]
        recs2k_end = recs_2k.index[-1]
        draw_span(ax, recs2k_bgn, recs2k_end, leftmost)
        recs_2k8 = recs.loc['2008':]
        recs2k8_bgn = recs_2k8.index[0]
        recs2k8_end = recs_2k8.index[-1]
        draw_span(ax, recs2k8_bgn, recs2k8_end, leftmost)
        plt.text(0, -0.15, "Shaded areas indicate US recessions",
          horizontalalignment='left',
          verticalalignment='center',
          fontsize=14,
          transform = ax.transAxes)
    except Exception as e:
        print(e)
        pass
    
def add_source(ax, source):
    plt.text(0, -0.1, 'Source: ' + source,
      horizontalalignment='left',
      verticalalignment='center',
      fontsize=14,
      transform = ax.transAxes)
    
    current_time = time.strftime("%m-%d-%Y %T %Z", time.localtime(time.time()))
    plt.text(0.95, -0.1, 'Date: ' + current_time,
      horizontalalignment='right',
      verticalalignment='center',
      fontsize=14,
      transform = ax.transAxes)
    plt.text(0.95, -0.15, "Copyright  2019, Bateman Capital",
      horizontalalignment='right',
      verticalalignment='center',
      fontsize=14,
      transform = ax.transAxes)

def fred_swap(old, ice, column_name):
    old_end = datetime.datetime(2014, 8, 1)
    swap_old = fred_reader(old)[:old_end].iloc[:,0]
    swap_ice = fred_reader(ice).iloc[:,0]
    swap = pd.concat([swap_old, swap_ice]).dropna().to_frame(column_name)
    return swap

start = datetime.datetime(2000, 7, 1)

swap_2y = fred_swap('DSWP2', 'ICERATES1100USD2Y', 'swap-2y')
swap_3y = fred_swap('DSWP3', 'ICERATES1100USD3Y', 'swap-3y')
swap_5y = fred_swap('DSWP5', 'ICERATES1100USD5Y', 'swap-5y')
swap_10y = fred_swap('DSWP10', 'ICERATES1100USD10Y', 'swap-10y')

swap2y = swap_2y["swap-2y"]
swap3y = swap_3y["swap-3y"]
swap5y = swap_5y["swap-5y"]
swap10y = swap_10y["swap-10y"]

ffr = fred_reader('DFF')[start:]

fig, ax1 = plt.subplots()

yaxis_label = 'rate'
ax1.set_ylabel(yaxis_label)
ax1.tick_params(axis='y')

ax1.plot(swap_2y, label='2yr Swap Rate')
ax1.plot(swap_3y, label='3yr Swap Rate')
ax1.plot(swap_5y, label='5yr Swap Rate')
ax1.plot(swap_10y, label='10yr Swap Rate')

# fed funds rate
ffr_label = 'Fed Funds Rate'
ax1.set_label(ffr_label)
ax1.plot(ffr, color='tab:red', label=ffr_label)

ax1.set_ylim(top=8.0)
ax1.legend(loc='upper right')
ax1.grid(alpha=0.3)

plot_recession(ax1, swap_2y.index[0])

# stretch
plt.subplots_adjust(left=0.1, right=1.0)
plt.title("Fed Funds Rate vs Swap Rates")

add_source(ax1, "Federal Reserve Bank of St.Louis, ICE")

def change(r):
    return ((r.shift(1) - r) / r).dropna()

c10y = change(swap10y)
c2y = change(swap2y)
swap_corr = c10y.rolling(20).corr(c2y).dropna()

cut = srvix.index[0]

fig, ax1 = plt.subplots()
ax1.plot(srvix, color='purple', label='IV')
ax1.set_ylabel('IV')
ax1.tick_params(axis='y')
ax1.set_ylim(bottom=50)

ax2 = ax1.twinx()
ax2.set_ylabel('corr')
ax2.plot(swap_corr[cut:], label='2y and 10y swap change corr')

ax3 = ax1.twinx()
ax3.spines['right'].set_position(('axes', 1.1))
ax3.set_ylabel('spread')
ax3.plot(spread_2s10s[cut:], color='green', label='2y10y spread')

ax2.set_ylim(top=1.3)
ax3.set_ylim(bottom=-0.8)
ax1.legend(loc='upper left')
ax2.legend(loc='upper right')
ax3.legend(loc='lower right')

plt.title("IV of 10yr swap (SRVIX) vs 2y10y spread vs 2y and 10y swap change correlation")
add_source(ax1, "Federal Reserve Bank of St.Louis, ICE, CBOE")

Right now, low IV, flat curve, high swap change correlation.
